{
  "texts": [
    "Corrigible agents: a model which allows our attempts to interfere with its behavior, including changing its programming or turning it off. 4.",
    "Myopic agents: a model which isn't optimizing any sort of coherent long-term goal.",
    "Rather, its goals are limited in some way. 5.",
    "Simulators: a model which only simulates some other process, not an agent following goals. 6.",
    "Narrow agents: a model which has a high degree of capability in a narrow range of domains, but severely constrained capability in all other domains. 7."
  ]
}